## The 8 Assessment Dimensions

| #   | Dimension                      | Scorer File             | Owner            |
| --- | ------------------------------ | ----------------------- | ---------------- |
| 1   | Security, Privacy & Compliance | `security_scorer.py`    | IT Security      |
| 2   | Vendor Viability & Continuity  | `viability_scorer.py`   | Procurement      |
| 3   | Integration & Data Integrity   | `integration_scorer.py` | IT / Engineering |
| 4   | Legal & IP                     | `legal_scorer.py`       | Legal            |
| 5   | Cost & Commercials             | `commercial_scorer.py`  | Procurement      |
| 6   | Operations & Change Management | `operations_scorer.py`  | Procurement / IT |
| 7   | Global Scalability             | `scalability_scorer.py` | IT / Engineering |
| 8   | Product Maturity & Delivery    | `maturity_scorer.py`    | AI Innovation    |

Each dimension is scored **0–100** and flagged 🟢 Green (≥70) / 🟡 Amber (40–69) / 🔴 Red (<40).

---

## Scoring Engine Architecture

### Scorer Pattern

All scorers extend `base_scorer.py` (`BaseScorer` abstract class). Each scorer implements:

1. **Rules-based scoring** — deterministic checks on structured intake form fields
2. **LLM-assisted scoring** — uploaded documents sent to OpenRouter with dimension-specific prompts

### Scoring Formula

```
Final Dimension Score = 0.6 × RulesScore + 0.4 × LLMScore
```

### LLM Integration

- Use OpenRouter API at `https://openrouter.ai/api/v1`
- Default model: `meta-llama/llama-3-8b-instruct:free`
- Document text is extracted, chunked if needed, then prompted with structured criteria
- Parse LLM response to extract numeric sub-score + reasoning text

